-- GM China Partner SAIC May Buy Stake in Automaker's IPO, Chairman Hu Says
-- Bloomberg News
-- 2010-09-20T10:26:42Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-20/gm-china-partner-saic-may-buy-stake-in-automaker-s-ipo-chairman-hu-says.html

          
          
             SAIC Motor Corp. may invest in
General Motors Co.’s initial public offering if conditions are
favorable, chairman Hu Maoyuan said in Shanghai.  
 The company hasn’t made a decision yet whether to make the
investment and it is waiting for the IPO details, he said. It
will closely watch the share sale, he said.  
          
          


  


        